  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 3 high, 11 medium, 24 normal. Key bases needing attention include Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Vienna (VIE/LOWW) and Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ); plus 1 other bases. 11 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and RVR limitations  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Vienna (VIE/LOWW) and Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ). Network hotspots: Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Karlsruhe Baden-Baden (FKB/EDSB), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Bergen Airport, Flesland (BGO/ENBR) and 3 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, mist and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Karlsruhe Baden-Baden (FKB/EDSB), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Haugesund Airport, Karmøy (HAU/ENHD) and 9 others.",
